contentrichtext.text: '''LTU''' may mean: *IATA code for [[Latur Airport]], India *[[La Trobe University]], a university in Australia *[[Lambda the Ultimate]], a weblog devoted to programming languages *[[Land treatment unit]], a term in bioremediation *[[Leeds Trinity University]] *[[Lawrence Technological University]], a university in Southfield, Michigan *[[Le Quy Don Technical University]], a university in Hanoi, Vietnam *[[Liaoning Technical University]], a university in China *[[Licence to use]], a type of intellectual property licence *Lietuvos Teisės Universitetas, present-day [[Mykolas Romeris University]] in Lithuania *[[Louisiana Tech University]], a university in Ruston, Louisiana *LTU, the country code for [[Lithuania]] as used by some governing bodies, notably the IOC and FIFA *[[LTU International]], a German airline *[[LTU Technologies]], a software company *[[Luleå University of Technology]], a university in Sweden {{disambig}}
